# Example sops-encrypted secrets file.
#
# This file is committed to the repo to show the shape of secrets the
# deployment expects. The real, encrypted version lives next to it as
# `secrets.yaml` (gitignored).
#
# What the plaintext side looks like — these are the keys you fill in
# when you run `sops secrets.yaml` for the first time:
#
#   team-bot-token: discord-bot-token-here
#   # anthropic-api-key: sk-ant-...
#   # future secrets here, one per line
#
# After `sops secrets.yaml` is run with the recipients in .sops.yaml,
# the on-disk file looks like this (placeholder blob — not a real
# decryptable value):
#
#   team-bot-token: ENC[AES256_GCM,data:<base64>,iv:<base64>,tag:<base64>,type:str]
#   sops:
#       age:
#           - recipient: age1placeholder...
#             enc: |
#               -----BEGIN AGE ENCRYPTED FILE-----
#               <encrypted ciphertext>
#               -----END AGE ENCRYPTED FILE-----
#       lastmodified: "2026-05-26T00:00:00Z"
#       mac: ENC[...]
#       version: 3.10.2
#
# See docs/secrets-bootstrap.md for the operator walkthrough.
